WEBVTT

00:09.095 --> 00:11.679
♪♪

01:09.762 --> 01:11.261
[cell door slams in distance]

01:24.345 --> 01:25.845
[door lock buzzes]

01:32.136 --> 01:33.428
[door slams]

01:36.720 --> 01:38.303
You arrest me
in front of my kids?

01:38.303 --> 01:40.345
Well, you fucking
lied to me.

01:40.345 --> 01:43.345
God, this is a miserable place,
Miami, right?

01:43.345 --> 01:44.720
Too fucking hot.

01:44.720 --> 01:46.136
I'm going to get
used to this in hell.

01:46.136 --> 01:48.387
It's good practice
for you too, though, huh?

02:00.387 --> 02:01.303
Hmm.

02:04.845 --> 02:06.136
You can keep that.

02:08.762 --> 02:10.845
I earned that 18 grand.

02:10.845 --> 02:12.470
The fuck you did.

02:12.470 --> 02:14.929
I didn't pay you
to tell me stories.

02:14.929 --> 02:16.637
Did you ever think
that maybe...

02:16.637 --> 02:19.929
maybe I thought the bodies
were in the truck?

02:19.929 --> 02:21.679
You know, I bet
you've probably

02:21.679 --> 02:23.178
heard this a lot
in your life, Jimmy,

02:23.178 --> 02:24.845
but not good enough.

02:24.845 --> 02:26.929
Don't fucking pull
that shit with me, Jackie.

02:26.929 --> 02:28.637
You gonna leave me here?
Huh?

02:28.637 --> 02:30.345
You didn't fly all the way
down to Miami

02:30.345 --> 02:31.887
to tell me to go
fuck myself.

02:31.887 --> 02:33.679
No. I came for my 18 grand.

02:33.679 --> 02:37.261
I thought the bodies
were in the fucking truck, okay?

02:40.512 --> 02:42.679
[sighs]
Fuck.

02:42.679 --> 02:43.929
Honest.

02:46.345 --> 02:48.720
Would I risk havin' happen

02:48.720 --> 02:51.178
what-what just happened
to me and my kids?

02:52.512 --> 02:54.220
I really believed
you, kid.

02:54.220 --> 02:58.178
But I guess that's what I get
for being an asshole.

02:58.178 --> 03:01.470
What your mother
has felt every day...

03:01.470 --> 03:03.220
-of her miserable life:
-Fuck.

03:03.220 --> 03:04.804
disappointment.

03:10.553 --> 03:12.303
You know...

03:15.178 --> 03:16.553
when I was a kid,

03:16.553 --> 03:18.303
I was pretty good
at left wing.

03:19.720 --> 03:21.136
Yeah.

03:21.136 --> 03:23.845
But my father...

03:25.136 --> 03:27.136
he would ride my ass,
you know?

03:27.136 --> 03:28.553
He would fucking
embarrass me.

03:30.470 --> 03:31.970
Every single game.

03:34.011 --> 03:37.053
But he was there, though,
every game.

03:37.053 --> 03:38.970
So when you go home tonight,

03:38.970 --> 03:40.804
at least you can
look your daughter in the eye

03:40.804 --> 03:42.428
while you disappoint her.

03:46.428 --> 03:47.387
Hmm.

03:52.470 --> 03:53.929
How did you know...

03:55.970 --> 03:57.720
that the truck was there?

03:57.720 --> 04:00.553
You know, the Lynn Marsh.
I mean, you didn't guess, right?

04:00.553 --> 04:04.595
You wouldn't risk having happen
what just happened.

04:07.637 --> 04:08.887
Hey.

04:11.512 --> 04:13.512
You know who killed
those guards, don't you?

04:16.929 --> 04:18.637
[Kick]
No. No.

04:18.637 --> 04:20.595
No! No!

04:20.595 --> 04:22.053
[Kick breathing heavily]

04:22.053 --> 04:24.261
Daddy! Daddy!

04:24.261 --> 04:25.720
-[Cathy] Kick? Kick?
-[Frankie] Catherine?

04:25.720 --> 04:27.261
Catherine, shh.

04:27.261 --> 04:28.762
Kick, sweetheart,
wake up.

04:28.762 --> 04:30.095
Hey, we're right here.
Kick, come on.

04:30.095 --> 04:33.345
-Oh!
-Easy, easy. Easy.

04:33.345 --> 04:35.387
Look at me. It's just a dream.
Sweetheart, it's just a dream.

04:35.387 --> 04:36.970
-Just breathe.
-[boy] What's wrong with her?

04:36.970 --> 04:38.512
-Go back to bed, honey.
-Mom, what's happening?

04:38.512 --> 04:39.887
Go back to bed, honey.
It's okay. It's all right.

04:39.887 --> 04:40.887
Come on, let's go.

04:40.887 --> 04:42.303
I'm here with you.

04:42.303 --> 04:44.053
Your father's
here with you.

04:44.053 --> 04:46.178
All right?
Everything's all right.

04:46.178 --> 04:48.970
What did you
dream about, huh?

04:48.970 --> 04:51.470
I was trapped
in this building,

04:51.470 --> 04:56.178
and there were all these
burnt-up bodies, and smoke.

04:56.178 --> 04:58.470
Like after a war
or something.

04:58.470 --> 05:00.804
-Yeah.
-And I got scared,

05:00.804 --> 05:03.136
'cause one of the bodies...

05:04.887 --> 05:06.679
was Uncle Jimmy.

05:06.679 --> 05:08.595
[Frankie]
Uncle Jimmy.

05:08.595 --> 05:10.387
He's fine.

05:10.387 --> 05:12.845
Okay?

05:12.845 --> 05:14.679
You needn't worry
about him.

05:39.637 --> 05:41.220
[man] From the size
of the fragment

05:41.220 --> 05:42.512
and the impact
of the steel,

05:42.512 --> 05:44.887
you're looking for some
military-grade weapons.

05:44.887 --> 05:45.845
And what kind?

05:48.011 --> 05:50.345
I mean, specifically?

05:50.345 --> 05:53.887
Christ, I've been
at this all week, you know.

05:53.887 --> 05:56.387
You're worse
than my wife.

05:56.387 --> 06:00.178
Yeah, okay. Well, you let us
know what you find

06:00.178 --> 06:04.970
after you run ballistics,
and I'll let your wife know

06:04.970 --> 06:07.720
that you're doing
God's work.

06:07.720 --> 06:09.804
So, what if your C.I.
doesn't tell you

06:09.804 --> 06:11.929
who killed the guards
or where the bodies are?

06:11.929 --> 06:14.720
Am I supposed to just wish
the grand jury a fond farewell?

06:14.720 --> 06:16.553
There comes a time
in every man's life

06:16.553 --> 06:18.136
when he's gotta hoist
the black flag

06:18.136 --> 06:19.887
and commence
slittin' throats.

06:19.887 --> 06:21.345
What, did you hear that
on a pirate ride

06:21.345 --> 06:23.136
at Disney World
or something?

06:23.136 --> 06:24.345
You're still looking at this

06:24.345 --> 06:25.470
like a fuckin'
asshole prosecutor.

06:25.470 --> 06:27.303
Slit throats. Play dirty.

06:27.303 --> 06:29.387
Grand jury's
not a fuckin' trial.

06:29.387 --> 06:31.095
You're not going
for a conviction.

06:31.095 --> 06:33.970
You-you asked Tommy Hayes
about that fuckin' Lynn Marsh--

06:33.970 --> 06:36.220
But I'm not allowed
to bring up Lynn Marsh.

06:36.220 --> 06:39.428
Lynn Marsh has nothing to do
with the Kinicki case, okay?

06:39.428 --> 06:41.637
I-I need to get the jurors
to see what we see

06:41.637 --> 06:43.428
so they can start asking
questions on their own.

06:43.428 --> 06:46.428
Let them connect Kinicki
to the heist in Revere.

06:46.428 --> 06:48.095
All right, well, so much for me
helping you, then.

06:48.095 --> 06:49.637
Is that what this is?

06:49.637 --> 06:51.929
Well, I'm out of practice
at being nice.

06:51.929 --> 06:53.095
I...

06:54.929 --> 06:56.470
[Eloise]
We found the bullet fragment.

06:56.470 --> 06:57.720
Who did?

06:57.720 --> 06:59.970
We did.
The state crime lab.

06:59.970 --> 07:02.303
Good. Let's celebrate.

07:02.303 --> 07:04.303
-Me and you.
-Oh, yeah.

07:04.303 --> 07:06.136
A saggy-balled,
whiskey-dicked old man

07:06.136 --> 07:07.387
is exactly what I need.

07:07.387 --> 07:08.762
[laughs]

07:08.762 --> 07:11.095
So, can your people
trace a fragment?

07:11.095 --> 07:13.470
Sure. They just need time.

07:15.011 --> 07:17.470
So, what do you say?
You gonna reconvene?

07:19.929 --> 07:22.095
[Eloise] You could wait
for more evidence.

07:26.261 --> 07:28.970
It's time to slit throats.

07:28.970 --> 07:30.970
[woman] Thanks for coming
to the church food drive,

07:30.970 --> 07:32.303
and don't forget
your raffle tickets.

07:32.303 --> 07:33.303
Here you go.

07:33.303 --> 07:34.887
Raffle is at 1:00 today.

07:34.887 --> 07:36.136
Tell your friends.

07:36.136 --> 07:37.470
Siobhan.

07:40.512 --> 07:43.220
I'm sorry for our
little dustup the other day.

07:45.053 --> 07:48.387
Reverend, have you heard
about the Bantu philosophy Ntu?

07:48.387 --> 07:50.220
I don't think I have, no.

07:50.220 --> 07:52.261
I'll give you
the short version.

07:52.261 --> 07:54.428
Ntu is the essence
of purer life

07:54.428 --> 07:56.470
which celebrates
our interdependence.

07:56.470 --> 07:59.011
Every one of us
has equal purpose.

07:59.011 --> 08:01.136
Well, you majored
in African Studies

08:01.136 --> 08:03.178
at Boston University,
I see.

08:03.178 --> 08:06.679
My husband and I work very hard
at being equals.

08:06.679 --> 08:08.053
Mmm.

08:08.053 --> 08:10.428
Sharing each other's lives,
our hopes.

08:10.428 --> 08:12.845
If you and I are to continue
working together,

08:12.845 --> 08:14.679
you must respect that.

08:14.679 --> 08:15.762
Him.

08:19.011 --> 08:20.178
I see.

08:21.470 --> 08:23.095
Of course.

08:23.095 --> 08:25.303
Ntu, hmm?

08:25.303 --> 08:27.095
I'll have to read up on that.

08:29.011 --> 08:30.512
-[whistling]
-[train passing overhead]

08:35.762 --> 08:38.512
[keys jingle]

08:38.512 --> 08:40.053
-[grunts]
-God damn! Come on, man!

08:40.053 --> 08:42.887
[man 1] Where your wallet at?
Where your wallet?

08:42.887 --> 08:45.011
[man 2] Yo, yo, shit!
He's a cop!

08:45.011 --> 08:46.053
[man 1] Go man,
let's go, let's go!

08:46.053 --> 08:47.178
[man 2] Shit, yeah.

08:52.178 --> 08:53.804
[grunts]

09:29.595 --> 09:31.261
[indistinct chatter]

09:40.720 --> 09:44.387
[chatter continues]

09:57.387 --> 10:01.136
[quiet chatter]

10:04.303 --> 10:05.470
[woman] I'll let you know
what I find out.

10:05.470 --> 10:08.136
We'll talk again tomorrow.
Thank you.

10:09.887 --> 10:11.136
Kayla.

10:11.136 --> 10:12.679
Hello. How are you?

10:12.679 --> 10:14.804
I'm still shaky.

10:16.303 --> 10:17.595
That day,
the shooting at the church,

10:17.595 --> 10:18.887
"shaky" doesn't come close
for me.

10:20.679 --> 10:23.261
I need to tell you something
about the reverend.

10:24.428 --> 10:25.970
Four years ago,

10:25.970 --> 10:27.679
the church took a trip
to Haiti

10:27.679 --> 10:31.637
to distribute food and medicine
after the hurricane.

10:31.637 --> 10:34.136
Our group went to the beach
one day after helping out,

10:34.136 --> 10:38.762
and the reverend made
some comments about my swimsuit.

10:40.136 --> 10:41.553
I thought the comments
were weird,

10:41.553 --> 10:43.512
but I brushed them off.

10:43.512 --> 10:47.804
I was up for
the AFC scholarship.

10:47.804 --> 10:50.011
Then, later at the hotel,

10:50.011 --> 10:53.595
he said he wished
he had a camera,

10:53.595 --> 10:56.303
so he could enjoy my figure
a little longer.

10:58.637 --> 11:00.970
Did he actually
ask you for photos?

11:00.970 --> 11:04.178
He said that I should take
the initiative,

11:04.178 --> 11:07.220
that then he'd know
how serious I was

11:07.220 --> 11:08.512
about my future.

11:11.220 --> 11:13.220
You didn't photograph yourself?

11:13.220 --> 11:15.011
Of course not.

11:15.011 --> 11:18.178
You know how creepy
that is from my reverend?

11:18.178 --> 11:19.512
Then there's no evidence.

11:21.053 --> 11:23.387
-Witnesses?
-Witnesses?

11:25.428 --> 11:27.303
I'm telling you
this happened.

11:27.303 --> 11:30.136
Haiti was four years ago.

11:30.136 --> 11:31.762
-Should that matter?
-No.

11:31.762 --> 11:34.595
But that's how the law works.
Timing matters.

11:34.595 --> 11:37.053
So, what do you want
to do now?

11:37.053 --> 11:37.970
Sue?

11:41.595 --> 11:43.387
I don't want money.

11:43.387 --> 11:45.220
But you wouldn't
mind some?

11:48.762 --> 11:49.804
Kayla.

11:49.804 --> 11:50.887
[slide door clicks open]

11:52.220 --> 11:54.512
Kayla, wait.

11:54.512 --> 11:57.428
-You don't believe me, do you?
-I'm not saying that.

11:57.428 --> 11:59.595
But why did you remain a member
of the congregation

11:59.595 --> 12:00.845
if he makes you
uncomfortable?

12:00.845 --> 12:03.178
So I should just run away?
They're my people.

12:03.178 --> 12:04.845
They won't be.

12:04.845 --> 12:07.428
If you do this, every single
member of that congregation

12:07.428 --> 12:08.595
will turn their back
on you.

12:08.595 --> 12:10.095
Your people,

12:10.095 --> 12:12.136
the ones you attend
Bible study with,

12:12.136 --> 12:14.387
who smile and chat you up
at church cookouts,

12:14.387 --> 12:16.428
they will drag your name
through the streets,

12:16.428 --> 12:18.220
and you'll be sitting at home,
alone,

12:18.220 --> 12:20.845
wondering why you waited
four years to come forward,

12:20.845 --> 12:23.387
and trying to figure out
if what happened--

12:23.387 --> 12:25.762
What you recall
actually went down that way.

12:28.345 --> 12:29.929
And what would you do

12:29.929 --> 12:33.595
if the reverend tells you
to take the initiative?

12:48.929 --> 12:51.762
I hope you know
what you're doing.

12:51.762 --> 12:53.428
Your Honor?

12:53.428 --> 12:54.804
This Kinicki case.

12:54.804 --> 12:58.053
These men,
Mr. Hayes and Mr. Sheehan,

12:58.053 --> 13:00.136
who you're bringing
before the grand jury.

13:02.804 --> 13:05.470
I'm not saying you're wrong
for taking a shot at this.

13:07.053 --> 13:09.387
Just don't miss.

13:09.387 --> 13:11.095
You're 0 and 1.

13:11.095 --> 13:14.845
Botch another case and,
affirmative action or not,

13:14.845 --> 13:17.970
the climate gets that much
harder for the next guy.

13:28.345 --> 13:30.095
Shoot straight.

13:31.845 --> 13:33.720
Nobody's in cuffs.

13:33.720 --> 13:35.637
Easy for you. You're not the one
who's gonna be sitting

13:35.637 --> 13:36.929
in front of the grand jury.

13:36.929 --> 13:39.470
Listen, this DA
fucking prick

13:39.470 --> 13:41.178
isn't joking around.

13:41.178 --> 13:43.679
He's a serious nigga,
I'm telling you.

13:43.679 --> 13:46.178
If you don't talk,
there's nothing he can do.

13:46.178 --> 13:48.136
No, well, there's contempt.

13:48.136 --> 13:50.345
They can hold us
till the grand jury is over.

13:50.345 --> 13:52.011
-How long is that?
-It don't matter.

13:52.011 --> 13:54.512
You go in there,
you answer a few easy questions.

13:54.512 --> 13:56.845
You say you forgot the rest.

13:56.845 --> 13:58.595
Like Nixon.

13:58.595 --> 13:59.720
Yeah, look what happened
to him.

13:59.720 --> 14:01.679
He was pardoned, right?

14:01.679 --> 14:03.387
Now, if they had dug up
enough about Kinicki,

14:03.387 --> 14:04.845
we'd be charged already.

14:04.845 --> 14:06.804
They're looking
for something else.

14:06.804 --> 14:09.178
What the fuck
are they after?

14:09.178 --> 14:10.637
Calm down.

14:10.637 --> 14:12.136
Shit comes with what we do.

14:13.804 --> 14:15.387
It's going to be
all right, dude.

14:15.387 --> 14:16.512
[Frankie]
Sheik...

14:16.512 --> 14:18.053
[sniffs]

14:18.053 --> 14:20.053
...none of this.

14:21.512 --> 14:22.637
How's Christie?

14:22.637 --> 14:23.929
She's all right.

14:23.929 --> 14:24.887
How are the kids?

14:28.887 --> 14:31.261
You're not worried
about me talking, are you?

14:31.261 --> 14:33.553
You? No.

14:33.553 --> 14:34.887
Him?

14:37.095 --> 14:38.970
I don't know, maybe.

14:40.929 --> 14:42.595
[Dermot]
Let's go, let's go. Nice.

14:42.595 --> 14:44.845
Knees up. Yeah.

14:44.845 --> 14:46.512
Let's see it.

14:46.512 --> 14:47.762
Love it.

14:47.762 --> 14:49.512
Let's go, let's go. let's go.

14:49.512 --> 14:52.095
Yes, one-two.
Find the space.

14:52.095 --> 14:54.345
Right knee over the ball.
Use your laces for the par.

14:54.345 --> 14:55.595
Go!

14:55.595 --> 14:56.887
Brilliant!

14:58.929 --> 15:00.470
-I can come back.
-Oh, no, nonsense.

15:00.470 --> 15:02.470
James is the real coach.

15:02.470 --> 15:05.303
I just offer advice,
whether needed or not.

15:05.303 --> 15:07.553
I actually need some.

15:09.428 --> 15:11.553
All right.
Come with me.

15:13.345 --> 15:15.095
It's beautiful here.

15:15.095 --> 15:17.637
Yeah, a stroll's a fine way
to clear the mind.

15:17.637 --> 15:19.261
Don't you agree, Mrs. Rohr?

15:19.261 --> 15:20.970
Please, Father,
call me Jenny.

15:20.970 --> 15:23.303
Well, you call me Dermot, then.
Seems only fair.

15:23.303 --> 15:24.804
"Deer-mut?"

15:24.804 --> 15:26.679
-[laughs]
-[exhales]

15:26.679 --> 15:29.720
Well you got a bit of an accent
there, but you're close enough.

15:31.303 --> 15:34.470
So, what dazzling wisdom
can I impart you?

15:34.470 --> 15:36.220
I, uh...

15:36.220 --> 15:39.136
I don't know if I'm doing
what I'm meant to be doing.

15:40.553 --> 15:41.970
Let's have a seat.

15:44.553 --> 15:46.804
You mean going back to school
for your teaching degree.

15:46.804 --> 15:48.470
Yeah. I mean...

15:48.470 --> 15:50.887
do you ever feel like
your whole life

15:50.887 --> 15:53.011
revolves around
one choice?

15:53.011 --> 15:55.970
I wasn't born
a priest, Jenny.

15:55.970 --> 15:58.679
Ya' know, when I told my mates
that I aim to take the vow,

15:58.679 --> 15:59.970
they thought I'd gone mad.

16:01.804 --> 16:03.637
Do you feel like
you missed out

16:03.637 --> 16:05.136
on something better?

16:07.136 --> 16:09.136
Yeah, now and again.

16:09.136 --> 16:11.303
You know, when I see new couples
at a baptism

16:11.303 --> 16:13.178
holding their baby.

16:13.178 --> 16:17.387
Yeah, I want that...
that connection.

16:17.387 --> 16:19.512
So...

16:19.512 --> 16:22.178
you regret
becoming a priest?

16:22.178 --> 16:24.470
Oh, no, no.
I made my choice.

16:24.470 --> 16:27.970
There's a million and two ways
my life could have turned out.

16:27.970 --> 16:30.095
But God only lets us
live the one.

16:30.095 --> 16:34.011
Our job is to find
the value in that life.

16:34.011 --> 16:35.679
Hmm.

16:35.679 --> 16:39.178
Yeah, I think I let too many
things get chosen for me.

16:40.512 --> 16:43.303
What do you want, Jenny?

16:43.303 --> 16:44.762
[sighs]

16:44.762 --> 16:47.136
I want my family to care...

16:48.512 --> 16:49.470
about me.

16:51.345 --> 16:54.178
My daughter used to, you know,
never want to let go of my hand,

16:54.178 --> 16:57.387
and now she, uh...
she barely talks to me.

16:57.387 --> 16:59.470
That doesn't mean
she doesn't love you.

16:59.470 --> 17:01.220
Yeah, I know.

17:01.220 --> 17:04.220
But she's spiteful.

17:05.595 --> 17:06.679
Like her father.

17:08.178 --> 17:09.470
And he drinks.

17:11.637 --> 17:12.762
She doesn't come home.

17:12.762 --> 17:15.011
I-I don't know who she's with,

17:15.011 --> 17:16.679
what's she's doing.

17:16.679 --> 17:17.887
I...

17:19.387 --> 17:21.845
I don't know how
to talk to her.

17:21.845 --> 17:23.720
How am I going to be
a good teacher?

17:23.720 --> 17:26.220
I can't even reach
my own daughter.

17:28.970 --> 17:31.136
I've been thinking
since we last talked.

17:31.136 --> 17:32.720
How would you feel
about volunteering here?

17:33.887 --> 17:35.595
At the school?

17:35.595 --> 17:38.303
Doing what?

17:38.303 --> 17:40.053
Well, the teachers are
understaffed and overworked.

